\fs40 \cf0 Relational Databases\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/Aditya-Bajpai-Consultadd/SQL-Practice#relational-databases"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\b0\fs32 \cf0 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs27\fsmilli13600 \cf0 Relational Database store information in the form of tables. Multiple tables share information between them causing them to have a relationship.\
Hence, the name relational database.\
\
In a relational database, every table has a defined number of columns that define the information being stored and rows that stores the actual data.\
Each table must have a unique column to uniquely identify every single row of the table. That column is named the primary key. To establish \
relationship between multiple tables foreign key concept is used. SQL is used to interact with a relational database to perform CRUD operations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

